paragraph.content:
an application under section 15, 16 or 17;
                        (Added 16 of 2014 s.
                        5)

section.def:
immigration officer (入境事務人員) means the holder of a rank specified in Schedule 1 to the
            Immigration Service Ordinance (Cap. 331);
                (Added 16 of 2014 s. 5)

paragraph.content:
give an interim direction as the Court thinks fit for securing the welfare
                    of the child concerned, or for preventing changes in the circumstances relevant
                    to determining the application;

for the procedure on an application for the return of a child, the
                    documents and information to be furnished and the notices to be given in
                    connection with the application;

for the giving of notices by or to a court for the purposes of Article 16
                    of the Convention and section 11 and the proceedings to which those
                    provisions apply;

subsection.def:
applicable information (適用資料), in relation to a child, means information
                about the child’s whereabouts or other circumstances relevant to locating the
                child;

subparagraph.content:
that authority has made an order providing for the return of the child
                        to the child’s home state via Hong Kong (whether or not also via another
                        jurisdiction);

paragraph.content:
authorizing or directing a police officer to recover the child (and to do
                    so with the assistance the officer requires and by force if
                    necessary);

authorizing or directing a police officer to take the recovered child to,
                    and keep the child in, a place of safety until the return or delivery of the
                    child to the specified person;

if the specified person cannot be contacted within a reasonable
                    time—authorizing or directing the Director of Social Welfare to take the
                    follow-up actions that the Director considers appropriate;

subsection.def:
custody application
                    (管養權申請), in relation to a child, means an
                application relating to the merits of rights of custody of the child;

rights of custody
                    (管養權) has the same meaning as in the provisions of
                the Convention set out in Schedule 1;

paragraph.def:
“rights of custody”
                    shall include rights relating to the care of the person of the child and, in
                    particular, the right to determine the child’s place of residence;

paragraph.content:
where the circumstances so require, to provide or facilitate the provision
                    of legal aid and advice, including the participation of legal counsel and
                    advisers;

a certificate or an affidavit emanating from a Central Authority, or other
                    competent authority of the State of the child’s habitual residence, or from a
                    qualified person, concerning the relevant law of that State;
